<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-01-23T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-01-23T05:00:00-05:00" n="238" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d238">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.689 Entry, Residence and
                            Establishment/2: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-01-23T12:00:00+02:00">January 23,
                                1936—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received January 23—10:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>13. Department’s instruction No. 240 of November 15, 1935. The Greek
                            Government agrees in principle to the proposed treaty negotiations and I
                            have submitted the draft forwarded with the Department’s instruction
                            under reference.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacVeagh</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>